Commentary Text: Navdeep Saini to Chakravarthy, no run, he doesn't want to get in line. Steps leg-side again, Saini follows him with a full toss and he clips it to Kohli at short midwicket. Has he caught that? Didn't seem too confident, but the umpires have gone upstairs and even the soft signal is out. Resolution isn't great with the zoomed-up replay, no way the third umpire can tell conclusively with the front-on angle. But a replay from behind shows that the ball is clearly on the ground, Will be not out. Kohli wasn't confident to start with, wonder how the soft signal came to be out

Commentary Text: Siraj to Tripathi, out Caught by Chris Morris!! Into the pitch from Siraj, allows the two-paced nature of it to take over. And then turns back to watch Morris pull off a brilliant catch diving forward at long-on. Tripathi is late on this as he tries to pull. Miscues it up in the air off the top half, which is why it goes much straighter than he wants. Still a lot of work to do for Morris. Runs in, covers ground, and shows great committment diving with both hands. Tripathi c Chris Morris b Siraj 16(22) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Washington Sundar to Morgan, out Caught by Udana!! There is no teeing off against Washington Sundar. Not in this tournament so far and certainly not tonight. Such game smarts from the off-spinner. Morgan moves leg-side looking to hit over extra cover. Sundar sees this and fires it through at back of a length. It's not a length Morgan can comfortably hoist. It climbs on him, takes the outside edge and because of the pace on it - around 98kph from Sundar - carries to short third man. Morgan c Udana b Washington Sundar 8(12) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Washington Sundar to Morgan, out Shubman Gill Run Out!! It's getting messier for KKR! Poor judgement of a run and Gill is comfortably short. So, Morgan premeditated the charge, didn't get the length and in the process of checking his shot, nearly spooned a catch to cover. Udana stops it on the bounce and fires in a flat throw to de Villiers who does the rest. There was never a single there and Shubman Gill knew it too. He just started walking even before the third umpire's call came. It was Shubman Gill call though. Shubman Gill run out (Udana/de Villiers) 34(25) [4s-3 6s-1]
